        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Piece of cake to solo. I go to sit on the stairs leading into the room right outside Verix's room. No wanderers will get close enough to you to agro. I am not sure If I need to, but I root DOT the one right in front of me before I pet up. I pet up on the stairs, then pull the one to the left, then the one across the room to the left. Then I move my pet in, and pull Verix's room. 4 in that room, and one in a secret doored closet on the far wall. </P><P>Prisoners have 5K and change for HP. Soldiers have 7K and change for HP. Decayed Kylong has just shy of 8K for HP (Verix PH). I am not too sure what Verix has for HP, the 4 times I have seen him, I was in a group. Also, I would assume you could not pull something past Verix without agroing him. </P><P>Pretty easy, with the caveat that I have never soloed Verix, so I cannot comment on how much of a bitch he is. I know he is doable solo as a necro once you land slow on him. </P><P>If you are still looking for critters, pull the wanderers around the water corridor. Only problem is quite often those are live Drovlargs, which makes it a bit more challanging with a pet. </P><P>Cheers,<BR>Ancagalon the Black<BR>Warlock - Terris Thule</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
